<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-11T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="18" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/1866a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-11T15:00:00-04:00">February 11,
                                1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>527. Personal for Churchill<note n="42" xml:id="d18fn42">Winston S.
                            Churchill, British Prime Minister.</note> from Hopkins.<note n="43" xml:id="d18fn43">Harry L. Hopkins, Special Assistant to President
                            Roosevelt.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>“Apropos of your telephone call I talked to the President last night, and he
                        sees no difficulty whatever in China sitting in on your Pacific Council in
                        London.”</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>